      <div class="faq-grid">
        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>How long does immigration document translation take?</h3>
          <p>Standard turnaround is 24 hours for most immigration documents. Police clearance certificates and driving licenses complete in 4-6 hours. Bank statements depend on length—typically 6-12 hours. Rush service available for urgent visa appointments with same-day delivery possible for morning submissions.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Do I need attestation before translation?</h3>
          <p>For MOHRE employment visas and certain GDRFA applications, yes. Police clearance certificates typically need apostille or embassy attestation before translation. Educational documents require full attestation chain for credential evaluation. We advise on requirements based on your specific use case to avoid unnecessary costs.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Which countries' documents do you translate?</h3>
          <p>We translate immigration documents from all countries. Common source countries include India, Pakistan, Philippines, Egypt, UK, US, and European nations. Documents in Arabic, English, Hindi, Urdu, Tagalog, Chinese, French, and other languages are within our capability.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>Can you translate documents for Golden Visa?</h3>
          <p>Yes. Golden Visa applications require comprehensive document packages including bank statements, police clearance, <a href="/personal/academic/degree/">educational certificates</a>, and family documents for dependents. We provide complete Golden Visa translation packages with consistent formatting across all documents.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>What format do translated documents come in?</h3>
          <p>We provide both digital PDFs and physical certified copies. Digital versions are emailed immediately upon completion for portal submissions. Physical copies with original MOJ stamps are couriered within Dubai same-day or next-day for other emirates.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>How do you ensure name consistency across documents?</h3>
          <p>Before translating, we confirm preferred name transliterations. If you've previously obtained translated documents or have Emirates ID, we match existing renderings. For new transliterations, we follow standard conventions while ensuring all documents in your package use identical name formatting.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
          <h3>What if my document is rejected by immigration?</h3>
          <p>MOJ-certified translations from accredited translators are accepted by all UAE immigration authorities. If any authority requests clarification or revision, we address it at no additional cost. Our translations carry our license number for verification through MOJ.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="faq-item">
